1. To use the ribbon commands, what menu and grouping of commands will you find the Insert and Delete command? 
Ribbon commands grouped based on the functions under different tabs. Users find that the Ribbon tabs in excel are easier to use as compared to menu and toolbar.

2. If you set a row height or column width to 0 (zero), what happens to the row and column?
Excel will hide the row

3. Is there a need to change the height and width in a cell? Why? 
It depends on the use case. Sometimes the cell content is not completely visible by default size of the cell, so in order to get a complete view of the content in the cell, we change the height and width of the cell.

4. What is the keyboard shortcut to unhide rows? 
Ctrl+Shift+(row number)

5. How to hide rows containing blank cells? 
Select the data range which contains the blank cells you want to hide.
Then click Home > Find & Select > Go To Special, see screenshot: ...
And in the Go To Special dialog, select Blanks option, and then click the OK button.

6. What are the steps to hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting in excel?
To filter for unique values, click Data > Sort & Filter > Advanced.
To remove duplicate values, click Data > Data Tools > Remove Duplicates.
To highlight unique or duplicate values, use the Conditional Formatting command in the Style group on the Home tab.
